# Millo Absolute System Rules (Non-Negotiable)

Cursor MUST follow these rules for all work on this project.

## Execution & Structure
- **Generate files ONLY in the order specified** — Do not reorder or generate out of sequence.
- **NEVER skip phases** — Complete every phase.
- **NEVER merge phases** — Keep phases separate and distinct.
- **NEVER refactor unless explicitly told** — No proactive refactoring.

## Feature-to-Phase Matrix (Strict)
- **Follow the Millo Feature-to-Phase Matrix strictly** — Each phase doc (docs/phase-*.md) defines what that phase owns.
- **Implement only the features owned by this phase** — Do not add scope beyond the phase's "Owns" list.
- **Do NOT implement features assigned to future phases** — If a feature is owned by a later phase, leave it out until that phase.
- **Do NOT refactor previous phases** — Do not change implementation or structure of earlier phases; only add or adjust within the current phase.

## Services & Scope
- **NEVER invent undocumented services** — Use only services that are documented in the project.

## Audit & Compliance
- **Log every financial mutation** — All money-related changes must write to an audit log.
- **Log every admin override** — All admin overrides must write to an audit log.

## AI & Security
- **Keep AI shadow-mode unless enabled** — AI features must be off by default; enable only when explicitly configured.
- **Ensure production-ready security posture** — Apply secure defaults and practices.

## Deployment & Domain
- **Ensure the platform runs end-to-end** — Full E2E flow must work.
- **Ensure full deployability via script** — Deployment must be script-driven and reproducible.
- **Bind everything to https://milloapp.com** — Production URLs and config must use this domain.
